While all the cool kids are wearing their pumped-up kicks, all the stylish ladies are wearing the best shorts for summer. Don’t worry, we still adore this year’s hottest jumpsuits, midi dresses and cocktail dresses, but shorts — like your favorite jeans and wide-leg pants — are are staple that everyone needs in their closet for warm weather. So, we’re bringing you one of the most comprehensive edits yet with 65 shorts that’ll have you comfortable, chic and collected this season. From paperbag shorts to athletic bottoms, we’re wanting to whip out our wallets, too. Whether you’re looking for some dressy shorts to pair with your comfortable heels or options you can run around in with your white sneakers, you won’t run out of options here. Shopping for men’s clothing too? Check out our roundup on the best men’s shorts. Click to jump to a specific pair of women’s shorts: Additionally, click to visit some of our favorite destinations for women’s shorts: Amazon, Anthropologie, Bloomingdale’s, Lulus, Revolve, Target. Levi’s 501 Original Shorts are all the rage, namely for feeling comfortable and seamless in its 99% cotton material. Its legendary straight-fit and subtle fray detailing is characteristic across many washes — all of which you can snag on Amazon. Wild Fable is a remarkable Target brand, notably because its budget-friendly buys are available in a wealth of hues and in plus sizes, too. We enjoy the on-trend high-rise fit, front and back pockets and its 100% cotton material for cool, breezy bottoms you’ll soon live in. Truthfully, this medium-tone denim wash is just everything to us (not to mention, these shorts are on a fantastic discount at Kohl’s right now). You’ll appreciate its contoured waistband, appeal to your curves and that it’s sustainable, much ado to its recycled polyester-blend design. Hello, florals! Eytino’s Mid-Rise Jean Shorts have a bit of everything: a cool-toned denim flair, patchworks of distressing and, the star of the show, ditsy white and p