et — all of which have a sought-after soft feel and high-rise waistband that contours with your body to move with you. Pick them up in every color — it’ll still be less than $50! We’re floored that Free People has a dreamy pair of biker shorts for just $30. Great for barre class or frolicking around your home on a weekend, its Hot Shot style comes in a vast variety of colors and feel like a second skin when you’re wearing them. We love all shorts but a pair that has built-in pockets automatically receives more brownie points. In a generous size range from XXS to XXL, they’re especially great for running and hug in all the right areas. Looking for flattering biker shorts? Offline by Aerie’s Real Me Xtra Pocket Bike Short is like none other, simply because its crossover detailing — just like its massively followed Crossover Super Flare Legging ($41) — is something we rave about IRL. Trust us — buy the pair. We love the unique print on Beach Riot’s Bike Short, especially for coming with a paired Anna Tank ($88) to make it a matching set. Style it with APL’s Techloom Breeze Sneaker ($220) and a few coats of Benefit Cosmetics’ Roller Lash Curling Mascara ($27) and you’ll be all set to be on-the-go in style. Impressively, Everlane’s well-made Seamless Bike Short is just $40, and we love its basic, quality fit. The flattering extra-high rise, forgiving ribbed waistband and its combination of organic cotton and recycled nylon deserve all the praise we can muster. We stole inspiration directly from Elle Woods’ closet with Beyond Yoga’s High-Waisted Biker Shorts. They’ll be your favorite punchy color in your closet, especially when styled with Madeworn’s Rolling Stones Tee ($165) and Nike’s dazzling Crater Impact Sneaker ($100). With nearly 2,500 positive ratings on Amazon, Anftfh’s Drawstring Elastic-Waist Shorts are a steal for just $15. They come in a wide range of color options, too, and we love the faint pocket detailing along with the casual-leaning tie waistband. Plus,